To run this project on your own computer follow these steps:

1. Clone the repository in your own IDE
2. Open a new terminal in your IDE
3. If you are not already in the PitchArea directory navigate to the directory using the cd command
4. Now you must create a virtual environment to do that copy and paste the following code in the terminal:

  Windows:
    1. python -m venv venv
    2. .\venv\Scripts\activate

  MAC/Linux:
    1. python3 -m venv venv
    2. source venv/bin/activate

5. Install the required packages using the command: pip install -r requirements.txt
6.  You should now be able to run the project with the line:

    Windows:
      python pitcharea.py

    MAC/Linux:
      python3 pitcharea.py


    
